	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, May 6th 2:13 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[4.05]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I currently have a choice between the following sets of leg items:<br><br>Gatorscale Leggings<br>7 ac +4 wis +15 hp wt 0.4<br><br>Gray Leggings<br>8 ac +2 str +2 wis +5 mana +5% increase to block skill wt 1.0<br><br>I checked monkly-business and didn't see any discussion of the skill increase percentages on some of the new Luclin equipment. Given the choice between the two of these, which do most of you think is better? Is the greater chance to block (if it really works) coupled with the additional ac enough to offset losing 15 hps? The weight is not an issue for me since I am well under my cap. <br><br>Thanks.<br>&nbsp;<br>Jheran 54 Human Monk<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=310212" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=310212</a><br>Victorex 33 Wood Elf Ranger<br><br></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
	   </form></table><ul>
<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=102088020278466></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f102088020278466><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=3&mid=102088020278466>RE: Leg equipment choice</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=3&mid=102088020278466#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=140616><span id=Guru>Victorex</span></a>, <span id=Guru>Guru</span><br><span id=notbold>55 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, May 8th 1:58 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[5.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Thanks for the input. These two pieces are so close in terms of stats that I still am not sure what to wear...which is why I asked the question.<br><br>The deciding factor I think will be if the block skill mod is actually effective or not. Here's my reasoning:<br><br>Based on ac and stats, not counting the skill mod, I would wear the gatorscale for the extra 15hp. After reading the posts in this forum I too agree that the 8hp=1ac formula is a good one.<br><br>However, if the skill mod allows you to block one additional hit during the course of a fight from a mob that averages over 15 per hit (which most blue cons do at my level) then that cancels out the lack of 15hp on the grey leggings, and they would be the superior choice. This of course goes out the window when fighting casters since the skill mod does nothing for you when a spell lands.<br><br>As I stated in the original post, I haven't seen anything about the skill mod gear and how effective it actually is. I'll try and do some log parsing myself to try and answer the question *sigh* but if any of you have a reliable source of information on the skill mods and whether they really make a difference I would love to see it.<br><br>Again thanks for the input. <br>&nbsp;<br>Jheran 54 Human Monk<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=310212" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=310212</a><br>Victorex 33 Wood Elf Ranger<br><br></td></tr>
